      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Vulcan Utopia'' (column, May 29):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Vulcan Utopia'' (column, May 29):</p>
        <p>David Brooks is being churlish: Al Gore isn't ignoring people for machines; he's looking at a people who embrace machines and allow them to mediate their cultural and social interactions, the results of which Mr. Gore duly analyzes. That isn't being ''bizarre''; that is being succinct, and yes, reasonable.</p>
        <p>Thomas Linder  New York, May 29, 2007</p>
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I don't know about David Brooks, but I would rather be ruled by reason than by fear.</p>
        <p>Elaine Lopez  Playa del Rey, Calif., May 29, 2007</p>
      </block>
